classitems.name: when
classitems.description:
Wraps an object that might be a value or a (3rd party) then-able promise into a new promise.
This is useful when you are dealing with an object that might or might not be a promise, or if
the promise comes from a source that can't be trusted.

return.description: Returns a promise of the passed value or promise

classitems.name: all
classitems.description:
Combines multiple promises into a single promise that is resolved when all of the input
promises are resolved.

params.name: promises
params.description: An array or hash of promises.

return.description:
Returns a single promise that will be resolved with an array/hash of values,
  each value corresponding to the promise at the same index/key in the `promises` array/hash.
  If any of the promises is resolved with a rejection, this resulting promise will be rejected
  with the same rejection value.
